# MLOps Assignment 4 – ML CI Pipeline

This repository implements a GitHub Actions Continuous Integration (CI) pipeline for validating a Machine Learning project environment.

The purpose of this assignment is to move from manual execution to automated validation by fixing and completing a GitHub Actions pipeline.

---

## Project Objective

The CI pipeline automatically performs several tasks to validate the machine learning environment and project configuration.

The workflow performs the following steps:

- Set up a Python environment
- Install project dependencies
- Perform a linter check
- Run a dry test to verify the ML environment
- Upload the project documentation as a GitHub artifact

---

## Repository Structure

project-root/

.github/  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;workflows/  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ml-pipeline.yml  

requirements.txt  
README.md  
train.py (or other ML training code)

---

## CI Pipeline Workflow

The GitHub Actions workflow performs the following tasks:

### 1. Checkout Repository
The workflow checks out the repository code so that the pipeline can access all project files.

### 2. Setup Python Environment
Python 3.10 is installed using the GitHub Actions setup-python action.

### 3. Install Dependencies
All project dependencies are installed using:

pip install -r requirements.txt

This ensures the environment contains all required machine learning libraries.

### 4. Linter Check
A linter step is included to validate the project code structure and style.

### 5. Model Environment Dry Test
The pipeline runs the following command:

python -c "import torch; print('Model environment ready!')"

This verifies that the machine learning environment is properly configured and that the required libraries are installed.

### 6. Upload Project Documentation
The workflow uploads the file:

README.md

as a GitHub artifact named:

project-doc

This artifact can be downloaded from the GitHub Actions run.

---

## Workflow Trigger

The GitHub Actions workflow is configured to run on:

- Push to all branches except main
- Pull requests

This ensures that any new changes to the repository are automatically validated.

---

## Technologies Used

This project uses the following technologies:

- Python 3.10
- GitHub Actions
- PyTorch
- MLflow
- Scikit-learn
- TensorFlow
- Pandas
- NumPy

---

## Expected CI Result

After pushing code to the repository:

1. GitHub Actions will automatically run the workflow.
2. The pipeline should complete successfully.
3. The workflow run will appear green in the Actions tab.
4. An artifact named project-doc will be generated.

